{"title":"What I’ve been reading","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/907520048/0/marginalrevolution~What-Ive-been-reading.html","date":1730958429000,"content":"<p>1. Edwin Frank, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Stranger-Than-Fiction-Lives-Twentieth-Century/dp/0374270961/ref=sr_1_1?crid=LBAUMKQ4MZN8&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Gr8mg18m78NNDrrMNBysxMaZwn6VqecH5PS6-kCT4zE.KU_U-hvAeuJKeKvb6oJh1bnrDW8Q66Q-4H5DfuJa_-w&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=edwin+frank+stranger+than+fiction&amp;qid=1730853807&amp;sprefix=edwin+frank+%2Caps%2C112&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Stranger Than Fiction: Lives of the Twentieth Century Novel</a>.  Very good short portraits of various classic novels, including Machado de Assis, Mann’s Magic Mountain, Dr. Moreau, Carpentier, Perec, and others.  At this point I am usually sick of such books but this one I stuck with as it is rewarding throughout.</p>\r\n<p>2. Peter Doggers, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Chess-Revolution-Ancient-World-Digital/dp/1454959231/ref=sr_1_1?crid=T4RDNGHWMU55&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.WTxbiP_2rRPAnBPKs6e6vw.IpZGSK5bOb5bbWopZ-Y9geHfXIFH3RVF-BblkWITHeg&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=The+Chess+Revolution%3A+From+the+Ancient+World+to+the+Digital+Age&amp;qid=1730853852&amp;sprefix=the+chess+revolution+from+the+ancient+world+to+the+digital+age%2Caps%2C126&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">The Chess Revolution: From the Ancient World to the Digital Age</a>, is a good book, though it is mostly interior to my current knowledge set.</p>\r\n<p>3. Rebecca Charbonneau, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Mixed-Signals-Communication-Across-Curtain/dp/1509556915/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2LZHRSPUMU7NQ&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.JXVxMCYOj0mWqF5xHNKoWQ.pEB-reKHtObAjxErnYm0WUXQd5eApFMrsEhvGmwG6OI&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Mixed+Signals%3A+Alien+Communication+Across+the+Iron+Curtain&amp;qid=1730853906&amp;sprefix=mixed+signals+alien+communication+across+the+iron+curtain%2Caps%2C80&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Mixed Signals: Alien Communication Across the Iron Curtain</a>.  This book fit well into my recent “Soviet science” reading program.  This is more of a “Cold War” book than a “UFO book.”  And I learned <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CTA-102\" target=\"_blank\">the full saga</a> behind the Byrds song “<a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OONsT-z1hc8\" target=\"_blank\">C.T.A. – 102</a>” for the first time.</p>\r\n<p>4. Geoffrey Wawro, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Vietnam-War-Military-History/dp/1541606086/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3ABA5PWI92COB&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.13mZmDGoTj9kaINE9ok5GqQF37ffYJF2CjKaLWddyu8.EUs0mS12uUR4CPVpFAuTiEgOAxVHb50QtNHUQSYJTjU&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=geoffrey+wawro+s+the+vietnam+war+a+military+history&amp;qid=1730853769&amp;sprefix=geoffrey+wawro%2Caps%2C141&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">The Vietnam War: A Military History</a>, is the single best book on its topic and is both intelligent and highly readable.</p>\r\n<p>Coming in 2025 is David Spiegelhalter, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Art-Uncertainty-Navigate-Chance-Ignorance/dp/1324106115/ref=sr_1_1?crid=UMOISZ5K38W8&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.IrcUf2fQR1cXaYBMIR1b4Q.Pejum5QXXgawxsSOF5Dr5znnwtYUjsZU9ElauaDbQpA&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=The+Art+of+Uncertainty%3A+How+to+Navigate+Chance%2C+Ignorance%2C+Risk+and+Luck&amp;qid=1730853956&amp;sprefix=the+art+of+uncertainty+how+to+navigate+chance%2C+ignorance%2C+risk+and+luck%2Caps%2C71&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">The Art of Uncertainty: How to Navigate Chance, Ignorance, Risk and Luck</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Legacy-Robert-Higgs-Christopher-Coyne/dp/1942951450/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3SOAGV5TDJQMO&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.h43IaUKaY6IHezbWCOhVqA.hHtm2Te68aDUqJIcEWUy_ZIrzQFbmFvAwZ30wFbzrX4&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=the+legacy+of+robert+higgs&amp;qid=1730854003&amp;sprefix=the+legacy+of+robert+higgs%2Caps%2C97&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">The Legacy of Robert Higgs</a>, edited by Christopher J. Coyne, is a very good collection for those interested in the topics Bob worked on.</p>\r\n<p>Louis Kaplow, law and economics professor at Harvard, rethinks merger analysis in <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Rethinking-Merger-Analysis-Louis-Kaplow/dp/0262049244/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2E1BVO7LLZP2G&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.-Lpmn-9uoAJ026IN8lDMlFLm0efy1tCheqNmss7GhQs.K_H6SzWvqAjxtFNDFk1lFYwv_KHUvXCzV4XBXzhWIos&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Rethinking+Merger+Analyses&amp;qid=1730854048&amp;sprefix=rethinking+merger+analyses%2Caps%2C132&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Rethinking Merger Analyses</a>.</p>\r\n<p>I have not yet had a chance to start Agustina S. Paglayan, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Raised-Obey-Education-Princeton-Economic/dp/069126127X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3SCV4744OML8K&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.kOWp3oJmAh7EqGBRxYoHqg.OEqhjWev0PsAIWe2rj2mGRNHmPvMXodwjZfLshOm4Bo&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Raised+to+Obey%3A+The+Rise+and+Spread+of+Mass+Education&amp;qid=1730854114&amp;sprefix=raised+to+obey+the+rise+and+spread+of+mass+education%2Caps%2C78&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Raised to Obey: The Rise and Spread of Mass Education</a>.</p>\r\n<p>John Cassidy has a forthcoming collection of readings, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Capitalism-Its-Critics-India-Company/dp/0374601089/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1UWAU9Y5R8ZVG&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.X-X3KIWr7kVaJBG398d2cg.37fpHHAeo6_nAheL1l9bmHuKAtBuc7DQ8yrFMQXBGeM&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Capitalism+and+its+Critics%2C+A+History%3A+From+the+Industrial+Revolution+to+AI&amp;qid=1730854154&amp;sprefix=capitalism+and+its+critics%2C+a+history+from+the+industrial+revolution+to+ai%2Caps%2C95&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Capitalism and its Critics, A History: From the Industrial Revolution to AI</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/what-ive-been-reading-261.html\">What I’ve been reading</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/907520048/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/907520048/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/907520048/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/907520048/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/907520048/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/907520048/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/what-ive-been-reading-261.html#comments\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/comments20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/what-ive-been-reading-261.html/feed\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/commentsrss20.png\" /></a> \r\n<div><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/what-ive-been-reading-261.html#comments\"><h3>Comment